<http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/200306/24/eng20030624_118797.shtml>

Vietnam: Dengue Fever Cases Continue to Increase
------------------------------------------------
Vietnam reported 9300 dengue fever infected people and 22 deaths from the
disease in the first 6 months of 2003. The figures represent year-on-year
increases of 2.5 times in terms of infected cases and 5.5 times in terms of
fatalities, according to a report released by the Vietnamese Ministry of
Health on Tue 24 Jun 2003.
In June alone, the dengue fever epidemic involved 61 cities and provinces
of the country, causing 1258 cases and 3 deaths. The localities with the
highest numbers of infected people include Ho Chi Minh City and the
southern provinces of Tien Giang, Dong Thap, and Ben Tre.
